Implemented Vercel Web Analytics for Astro project

## Changes Made

### 1. Added @vercel/analytics package
- Installed `@vercel/analytics@^1.6.1` using npm
- Updated package.json with the new dependency
- Updated package-lock.json with locked dependency versions

### 2. Integrated Analytics component in Layout.astro
- Added import statement: `import Analytics from '@vercel/analytics/astro';`
- Placed `<Analytics />` component in the `<head>` section of the base layout
- This ensures analytics tracking is available on all pages that use this layout

### 3. Verified implementation
- Successfully built the project with `npm run build`
- Build completed without errors
- Analytics component will now track page views and visitor data once deployed to Vercel

## Files Modified
- `/src/layouts/Layout.astro` - Added Analytics import and component
- `/package.json` - Added @vercel/analytics dependency
- `/package-lock.json` - Updated with new dependency lock information

## Implementation Details
Following the Astro-specific instructions from the Vercel Web Analytics guide:
- Used the `@vercel/analytics/astro` import path for Astro framework support
- Placed the component in the head section as recommended for Astro projects
- This implementation provides automatic route support for Astro applications

## Next Steps
After deployment to Vercel:
1. Enable Web Analytics in the Vercel dashboard (Project → Analytics tab → Enable)
2. Deploy the application using `vercel deploy` or via Git integration
3. Verify analytics are working by checking for `/_vercel/insights/view` requests in the browser Network tab
4. View analytics data in the Vercel dashboard under the Analytics tab

The implementation preserves all existing code structure and only adds the necessary analytics tracking functionality.
